Package: ggped
Type: Package
Title: Draw Pedigree Charts Using ggplot2 and kinship2
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Moritz", "Lindner", email = "moritz@lindnerlab.de",
           role = "aut",
           comment = "Original ggped author, https://github.com/moritzlindner/ggped"),
    person("Shuai", "Yuan", email = "yuans@pitt.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = "Multi-feature segmentation, new geoms, and bug fixes")
    )
Description: A set of functions and geoms to draw pedigree charts from pedigree
    data created with kinship2. Extends the original ggped package with
    multi-feature segmented symbols (up to 4 features per individual), each with
    independent continuous or discrete colour mapping. Fork of
    <https://github.com/moritzlindner/ggped>.
License: GPL-2
URL: https://github.com/yuans-cellbio/ggped
BugReports: https://github.com/yuans-cellbio/ggped/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
    ggplot2 (>= 3.4.0),
    grid,
    grDevices,
    kinship2,
    tidyr,
    cli,
    scales,
    gtable
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
